					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114" rend="visible">
						<summary>An elaborate work on the Hafṭarot according to the German rite, as used in a town of Northern Italy, by Moses Romanini.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="v" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114">
							<locus from="1r" to="88v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maḥzor minhag Ashkenaz le-Shavuʻot ule-Sukot </title>
							<title n="0" xml:lang="he">מחזור מנהג אשכנז לשבועות ולסוכות ‬</title>
							<note>
								<p>The work is divided into 26 chapters.</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="illustration">A wood-cut representing an archway (excerpted from Daniel Bomberg's edition of the Hafṭarot, Venice 1548).<locus n="1r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="illustration">
								<locus n="6r, 7r, 11r, 13r, 16r, 22r,  23v, 25r, 27r, 29r, 34v, 41r, 42v, 46r, 48v, 50v, 51v, 52v, 53r, 56r, 60r, 65r, 76v, 82r, 83r, 85v, 86v"/>A pen and ink representation of human head at the begininng of chapters.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="diagram">Diagrams.<locus n="21v, 22v, 33r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="paratext">
								<locus n="20v"/>Musical notes.</decoNote>
